SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04599191
Version: 1

HPSBST03196 rev.1- HP StoreEver MSL6480 Tape Library running OpenSSL, Remote
Code Execution

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2015-03-17
Last Updated: 2015-03-17

Potential Security Impact: Remote code execution

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP StoreEver
MSL6480 Tape Library running Bash. This is the Bash Shell vulnerability known
as "Shellshock" which could be exploited remotely to allow execution of code.

References:

  CVE-2014-6271 (SSRT101816)

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.

  HP StoreEver MSL6480 Tape Library firmware versions prior to v4.60

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2014-6271    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       10.0
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has released the following firmware update to resolve the vulnerability
for HP StoreEver MSL6480 Tape Library.

  HP StoreEver MSL6480 Tape Library firmware v4.60 (available December, 2014)

The update can be found at the following location:

  Go to http://www.hp.com

  1. Click on "Support"

  2. From the pull-down, select "Drivers & Downloads"

  3. In the Find my Product field, enter "MSL6480"

  4. Expand the "HP StoreEver MSL6480 Tape Library " entry

  5. Select "HP StoreEver MSL6480 Scalable Base Module"

  6. Select "OS Independent" for the operating system

  7. Expand the "Firmware  Storage Tape" entry

  8. Download the most recent library firmware file, such as
HP_MSL6480_4.60.frm

